                    <msContents>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <locus from="3ra" to="26rb"/>
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1097Ammest">ʾAmmǝstu ʾaʿmāda mǝśṭir</title>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                                <locus from="3ra"/>
                                <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1097Ammest#Introduction">ʾAmmǝstu ʾaʿmāda mǝśṭir: Introduction to the Five Pillars of Mystery</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ንወጥን፡ በረድኤተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ጽሒፈ፡ መቅድመ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ርትዕት፡ ወፍኖተ፡ 
                                    አምልኮ፡ ጽይሕት፡ ዘጼሕዋ፡ አበዊነ፡ ሐዋርያት፡ ወአርትዕዋ፡ ወአብርህዋ፡ ውስተ፡ ኵሉ፡ ዓለም፡ ወደሰያት፡ ወተለውዋ፡ ፸ወ፪አርድእት፡ ፫፻፲ወ፰ርቱዓነ፡ ሃይማኖት፡
                                    መምህራኒነ፡ ሊቃውንት፡ ጸሎቶሙ፡ ተሀሉ፡ ምስለ፡ ፍቁሮሙ፡ ገብረ፡ መስቀል፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ </incipit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                                <locus from="9va" to="26rb"/>
                                <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1097Ammest#Trinity">ʾAmmǝstu ʾaʿmāda mǝśṭir: Mystery of the Trinity ()</title>
                            </msItem>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                            <locus from="26rb" to="38rb"/>
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2314senafe">Śǝna fǝṭrat (General record)</title>
                            <note>This composition normally follows the <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1097Ammest">ʾAmmǝstu ʾaʿmāda mǝśṭir</ref>, but in a few manuscripts
                                it is placed, as here, after the Mystery of the Trinity.</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
